Life, and all its trivial considerations; it took me all too long to realize that considerations were mere trifles, and that these preoccupations were for the myopic. These were what kept me spinning in the same damn spot all these years. It took a chemical intervention for me to realize this, to realize that the mind is a petty and limiting thing. It was my own damn brain that was responsible for my unhappiness. So don't trust it. Don't trust its interminable fret. In short: don't look, just leap. #manicmornings #helpmypersonalityissplitting
